Sitrin Capital Management LLC Reduces Stake in Costco Wholesale Corporation (COST)

					Posted by Jesse Mackey on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 



Sitrin Capital Management LLC cut its position in  Costco Wholesale Corporation (NASDAQ:COST) by 0.5% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The institutional investor  owned 28,058 shares of the retailer’s stock after selling 154 shares during the period. Costco Wholesale Corporation makes up  approximately  3.4% of Sitrin Capital Management LLC’s holdings, making the stock its 13th largest position. Sitrin Capital Management LLC’s holdings in Costco Wholesale Corporation were worth $4,705,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Other institutional investors have also recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Bank of New York Mellon Corp increased its position in  Costco Wholesale Corporation by 1.3% in the first quarter. Bank of New York Mellon Corp now owns 6,254,387 shares of the retailer’s stock worth $1,048,798,000 after buying an additional 79,201 shares in the last quarter.  Ameriprise Financial Inc. increased its position in  Costco Wholesale Corporation by 62.0% in the first quarter. Ameriprise Financial Inc. now owns 4,583,281 shares of the retailer’s stock worth $768,568,000 after buying an additional 1,753,741 shares in the last quarter.  Norges Bank purchased a new position in  Costco Wholesale Corporation during the fourth quarter worth approximately $553,367,000.  American Century Companies Inc. increased its position in  Costco Wholesale Corporation by 15.2% in the first quarter. American Century Companies Inc. now owns 2,197,302 shares of the retailer’s stock worth $368,466,000 after buying an additional 289,788 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Swiss National Bank increased its position in  Costco Wholesale Corporation by 26.2% in the first quarter. Swiss National Bank now owns 1,597,008 shares of the retailer’s stock worth $267,802,000 after buying an additional 331,400 shares in the last quarter. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  73.91% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Costco Wholesale Corporation alerts:



Costco Wholesale Corporation (COST) opened at 150.44 on Friday. The firm’s 50 day moving average price is $164.54 and its 200-day moving average price is $168.41. Costco Wholesale Corporation has a one year low of $142.11 and a one year high of $183.18. The company has a market capitalization of $65.98 billion, a PE ratio of 26.12 and a beta of 0.94.  Costco Wholesale Corporation also was the recipient of some unusual options trading on Thursday. Stock investors bought  6,031 put options on the company. This is an increase of 231% compared to the average volume of 1,822 put options.




Costco Wholesale Corporation (NASDAQ:COST) last issued its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, May 25th. The retailer reported $1.40 EPS for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $1.31 by $0.09. Costco Wholesale Corporation had a return on equity of 20.45% and a net margin of 2.06%. The firm had revenue of $28.86 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $28.57 billion. During the same period in the prior year, the firm posted $1.24 EPS. The company’s revenue for the quarter was up 7.8% on a year-over-year basis.  Equities analysts forecast that  Costco Wholesale Corporation will post $5.77 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
