In related news, CFO Anne H. Lloyd sold 6,472 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Wednesday, May 3rd. The shares were sold at an average price of $238.73, for a total value of $1,545,060.56. Following the sale, the chief financial officer now directly owns 69,941 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $16,697,014.93. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is available through this hyperlink. Also, Chairman C Howard Nye sold 10,258 shares of Martin Marietta Materials stock in a transaction that occurred on Wednesday, May 3rd. The shares were sold at an average price of $239.16, for a total transaction of $2,453,303.28. Following the transaction, the chairman now directly owns 143,038 shares in the company, valued at $34,208,968.08. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders sold 18,121 shares of company stock worth $4,332,440 over the last three months. Corporate insiders own  1.06% of the company’s stock. 
Martin Marietta Materials Company Profile
Martin Marietta Materials, Inc is a supplier of aggregates products (crushed stone, sand, and gravel) used for the construction of infrastructure, nonresidential, and residential projects. Aggregates products are also used for railroad ballast and in agricultural, utility and environmental applications.







